<subSubSection pageId="119" pageNumber="877" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="119.[2018,2612,1575,2003]" pageId="119" pageNumber="877">
<collectingRegion box="[2019,2066,1654,1687]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="119" pageNumber="877">See</collectingRegion>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[2080,2221,1654,1687]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="egregius">L. egregius</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[2240,2461,1654,1687]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pfeifferi">Lasiurus pfeifferi</taxonomicName>
was previously considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[2481,2612,1694,1727]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="borealis">L. borealis</taxonomicName>
based on morphology, and restriction-enzyme analysis of mtDNA tentatively considered it a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rhoads" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[2335,2497,1812,1845]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="seminolus">L. seminolus</taxonomicName>
. Recent molecular studies based on mtDNA and nDNA maintained 
<taxonomicName box="[2295,2430,1891,1924]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pfeifferi">L. pfeifferi</taxonomicName>
as a distinct species. 
<taxonomicName box="[2136,2355,1930,1963]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="119" pageNumber="877" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pfeifferi">Lasiurus pfeifferi</taxonomicName>
is included in the Red Bat group. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
